<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-12-01T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-12-01T14:00:00-05:00" n="54" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d54">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">611.2131/253: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Whitehouse</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-12-01T14:00:00-05:00">December 1, 1934—2
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>66. Your 92, November 23. Trade Agreement Organization has about
                            completed consideration of changes in agreement to be proposed to
                            Colombia. The proposed changes will be incorporated in a memorandum to
                            be transmitted to Colombian Legation in Washington within the next few
                            days. The substance of the proposed changes will be sent to you by air
                            mail immediately the note is despatched.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>